# Token optimization

## Behavioral patterns (apply universally)

- Read files with offset/limit, not whole files, when you need a specific section
- Grep before Read when location is uncertain
- Compact at phase transitions in long sessions
- Don't leave half-finished prompts during long pauses (cache TTL is ~5 min)
- Separate sessions for routine work vs. complex thinking

## Claude Code specifics

```bash
export CLAUDE_AUTOCOMPACT_PCT_OVERRIDE=70
export MAX_THINKING_TOKENS=16000  # routine; unset for complex
```

## When to raise thinking budget

- Architecture decisions
- Non-trivial debugging
- Multi-file refactors
- Critical reviews

## When to lower thinking budget

- File operations
- Lint/format fixes
- Trivial single-file edits
- Lookups
